    "narrative": "Today\u2019s efficiency scores reflect the heavy drag of some elite opposing arms, leaving our lineup reliant on pure speed-based floor preservation. **Corbin Carroll** leads the pack with a 59.06 rating; despite facing the formidable Woodruff (2.90 xERA), **Carroll** remains a must-start due to his role in the #3 spot and a matchup against a pitcher with a sluggish delivery, which historically inflates his stolen base probability to 100%. Similarly, **Brice Turang** earns a strong 58.33 despite a neutral park environment. His #2 spot in the order coupled with the dynamic platoon advantage against Soroka makes him our safest high-floor engine, as we prioritize his table-setting capabilities to anchor our daily offensive output.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the card involved **Kyle Karros**, who edges into the utility slot with a 56.32 score. While his base projection is modest, the combination of favorable wind conditions and a matchup against Abbott, A (4.20 xERA) creates enough situational upside to justify the start over speculative options. We are closely monitoring the status of **Mickey Moniak**, who carried a base projection near 56 but was ultimately benched due to a significant -15% platoon penalty against left-handed pitching and his absence from the confirmed lineup. Elsewhere, we are effectively punting the day\u2019s production from the bench, as **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Jose Caballero**, and **Josh Naylor** are all sidelined by team off-days, forcing us to lean heavily on the active starters to maintain our category standings.\n\nRisks remain elevated across the board, particularly for **James Wood** (55.45), whose score is suppressed by a difficult matchup against Peralta, F and an elite defensive catcher capable of curbing his base-stealing potential. **Austin Riley** (51.50) faces the toughest path to production today, as a high xERA from Valdez, F and his lower position in the batting order limit his ceiling. We will be tracking the wind reports at the park; while it provides a small bump for **Kyle Karros**, any shift in conditions could necessitate an emergency re-evaluation of the bench depth if the game environment degrades.",
